        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 4 at 6:46PM MDT by NWS Great Falls MT</headline>
        <description>At 641 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking thunderstorms along
a line extending from near Lincoln to Montana City to near Toston
with the strongest cell near Toston. Movement was northeast
at 35 mph. In addition to lightning, wind gusts up to 50 mph may
accompany these storms with brief heavy rainfall and pea-sized hail
possible with stronger cells.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Helena, Townsend, Lincoln, East Helena, Montana City, Wolf Creek,
York, Alhambra, Spring Meadow Lake State Park, Austin, Marysville,
Tower Rock State Park, Winston, Craig, Silos, Clancy, Canyon Creek,
Black Sandy State Park, Blossburg, and Goose Bay.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
